  "duration": 129.405310976,
  "text": " Is your organization built on purpose and meaning? Adaptable organizations are built on purpose and meaning, organized for effectiveness and efficiency, optimized for the future workforce, designed for human-centered realities. In uncertain times, organizations need to adapt quickly to change. Working without a clear purpose creates lower engagement and reduces connection to our teams, peers, and customers. That lack of purpose and meaning becomes so loud, it becomes challenging to adapt to what's next, leading to burnout and increased turnover. Adaptable organizations start with an understood purpose that connects your team, customers, and communities. Successful teams are formed around a clear purpose. One focused mission to keep the objective simple. creating flexibility and accountability to respond to new challenges, such as changing consumer behaviors and industry disruptors To build purpose and meaning help your organization find balance between the agility of mission teams and efficiency of traditional enterprise In what areas do fluid startup-inspired teams make the most sense? What tried-and-true mission-critical operations need to stay intact? What functions can be automated? Resist the temptation to add layers of unnecessary oversight. Workforce alignment around a shared purpose and the transparency afforded by technology can dramatically reduce the need for micromanagement. Clarity of purpose and connection to your organization's meaning drives the triple bottom line, increasing economic efficiency, cultivating people, and impacting positive community outcomes. Adaptable organizations employ diverse, cross-functional teams energized with purpose who can adapt quickly to whatever lies ahead.",
